Damus! since all are bom to die, Remember, in adversity, To show thyself resigned ; Nor less when Fortune's favouring gale Impels thy bark with ewelling sail, Maintain a placid mind.

Her gloomy shadows o’er the past, Or Indolenoe and Ease

Have seen thee woo the vernal wind

And quaff the purple grape‚ reclined Beneath the waving trees;
